Afrobeats singer Yemi Alade has expressed immense gratitude to late Ada Ameh for blessing her with her presence on her ‘Double Double’ musical video. She recounted how the actress brightened her mood when she noticed she was having a bad day even though it was their first time meeting. Alade prayed to God to grant the Ameh’s family, particularly ‘Grand ma’ the fortitude to bear such a devastating loss.   New ride confirms my big girl status – Cuppy     American record label welcomes Asake to fold     Simi reacts after dancer jumped on Adekunle Gold   She said: “I was having a bad day the first time I met you and I don’t know if anyone noticed but YOU instantly made me FEEL good. “I thanked you over and over again! You didn’t have to but you did! Most people will avoid it or act like I have a problem with them! Sigh… “This is how I will always remember you! Our Video Doubledouble is 5million views and counting. If I had stayed in that bad mood, I might have ruined it. “Thank you for blessing me Mama Ada Ameh, I pray your family (especially Grand ma) have the strength they need to bear this loss.”